column31: Chart requested by D Lennard "A straight line means constant compound daily growth, which is indeed the case."

Response by commenter Fleur Howles "It will not be constant compound daily growth. At some point the infection rates drop as the virus runs out of hosts. At this point the curve starts to level out. This is why an S curve is the right representation."
